                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#63v" facs="064">Fol. 63v</locus><desc>The death of ???: lower, laying in state before weeping mourners; upper, rejoicing in heaven among the <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s (who are playing horns)</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Digitized by Wendy Laura Belcher with Selamawit Mecca in January 2011 with a Canon Powershot outdoors at the Qʷaraṭa Walatta P̣eṭros Monastery on the eastern shore of lake Ṭānā. EMML 8471
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#2r" facs="002"> f. 2r and following</locus><locus target="#129v #64r #23r #70r #76r #29v #81v #87v #36r #93v #100r #2r #105v #111v #118r #12r #123v #135v" facs="130 064 023 070 076 030 082 088 036 094 100 002 106 112 118 012 124 136">129v, 64r, 23r, 70r, 76r, 29v, 81v, 87v, 36r, 93v, 100r, 2r, 105v, 111v, 118r, 12r, 123v, 135v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Arranged by later hands for the months of the year:
                    Ḫǝdār (129v)
                    Taḫśāś (64r)
                    Ṭǝrr (23r and 70r)
                    Yakkātit (76r)
                    Maggābit (29v and 81v)
                    Miyāzyā (87v)
                    Gǝnbot (36r and 93v)
                    Sane (100r)
                    Ḥāmle (2r and 105v)
                    Naḥāse (111v)
                    Maskaram (f. 118r)
                    Ṭǝqǝmt (f. 12r and 123v)
                    Pagʷāme (?)
                    monthly (<foreign xml:lang="gez">በበወርሑ፡</foreign>) (f. 135v)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገዳመ፡ ቆራጣ፡ ወለተ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ገድለ፡ ገላዴዎስና፡ ገድለ፡ ወለተ፡ ጴጥሮስ</foreign> The monastery of Qoraṭa Walatta P̣eṭros, The acts of Galāwdewos and Acts of Walatta P̣eṭros, written in red ink.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#1v" facs="002">Fol. 1v</locus>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record of a family dispute about inheritance, dated 1924, AM, Naḥāse 12. It mentions parties, judges, witnesses and the final judgement.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#13r" facs="013"> f. 13r and passim</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Mention or the original patron of the book, Galāwdewos and his wife, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፀደለ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#114r" facs="114">Fol. 114r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      Mention of the owner Galāwdewos again, and also his mother, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ጽዮን፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#152v" facs="153">Fol. 152v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    EMML No 8471  and Seal of the Derg/EMML Project. Recorded with Microfilm, property of Qʷarata Walatta P̣eṭros Monastery, Miyāzyā 3, 1978 AM
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#Inside back cover" facs="153">Fols. Inside,, </locus>
                    <q>
                    “AM OR IV 705”
                    </q>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
